Interface MonitorReport

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    ActionSkipper, AgeMonitor, ChannelMonitor, DBQuery, DBRecord, ExpectedLog, FileComparator, FileMonitor, FileTester, FTPTester, GenericList, IncrementalMonitor, JMSHealthChecker, JMSLogMonitor, JMSMonitor, JMXQMonitor, JVMMonitor, LatestRecord, Monitor, MultiFileMonitor, NumberMonitor, ProcessMonitor, PropertyMonitor, QMFQMonitor, QReportQuery, QueueMonitor, RedisTester, Report, ReportAggregator, ReportQuery, RMQMonitor, ScriptLauncher, ServiceMonitor, SonicMQMonitor, StaticReport, SyntheticMonitor, SysDataCollector, UnixlogMonitor, URLMonitor, WebOperator, WebTester, WinlogMonitor

    public interface MonitorReport
    MonitorReport is an Interface to get a report on a monitored entity
    Author:
    yannanlu@yahoo.com

    • Method Detail

      • generateReport

        java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.Object> generateReport(long currentTime)
                                                         throws java.lang.Exception
        generates a report on a monitored entity and returns it as a Map. The report Map will be passed to the associated MonitorAction as an opaque object. The action object is supposed to know how to retrieve the information from the report Map.
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception
